\sum_{i=1}^n \frac{i}{(i+1)!}=1- \frac{1}{(n+1)!}
1- \frac{1}{(n+2)!}
1-\frac1{(n+1)!}+\frac{n+1}{(n+2)!} = 1-\frac{n+2}{(n+2)!}+\frac{n+1}{(n+2)!} = 1-\frac{1}{(n+2)!}.
n=k
n=k+1
 1-\cfrac{1}{(k+1)!}+\cfrac{k+1}{(k+2)!}.
 1+\cfrac{-k+-2+k+1}{(K+2)!}=1-\cfrac{1}{(k+2)!}
\frac{n}{(n+1)!}=\frac{n+1-1}{(n+1)!}=\frac{n+1}{(n+1)!}-\frac{1}{(n+1)!}=\frac{1}{n!}-\frac{1}{(n+1)!}
